# Data Availability

This folder is intended for storing **raw sequencing data** (e.g., FASTQ, BAM) used for mRNA quality analysis.

---

## How to Obtain Data
To run the analyses in this project, download publicly available sequencing datasets:

- **RNA-seq (cDNA and direct RNA sequencing)**  
  NCBI SRA BioProject: **PRJNA856796**  
  [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/bioproject/PRJNA856796](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/bioproject/PRJNA856796)

- **Plasmid resequencing data**  
  NCBI SRA BioProject: **PRJNA854780**  
  [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/bioproject/PRJNA854780](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/bioproject/PRJNA854780)

- **E. coli reference genome** (for contamination checks)  
  Accession: **NC_000913.3**  
  [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3)

- **Supporting processed files**  
  DRYAD repository:  
  [https://doi.org/10.5061/dryad.s1rn8pkds](https://doi.org/10.5061/dryad.s1rn8pkds)

---

## Usage
1. Download the datasets from the above links.  
2. Place the raw FASTQ/BAM files in this `raw/` folder.  
3. The analysis scripts (`scripts/analyze_mRNA.py`) and notebooks will look for data here.  
##  Note on Usage
- These datasets are **not stored directly in this repository** (due to size).  
- To reproduce or extend the analyses:
  1. Download FASTQ/BAM files from the above accession links.  
  2. Place raw data inside the `data/raw/` folder.  
  3. Use the provided scripts (`scripts/analyze_mRNA.py`) and the Mana toolkit to perform QC and analysis.  

---

